dbp:altText: An elderly woman with glasses and white hair, wearing a pink jacket, rises to speak from the rearmost crossbench of the Chamber of the House of Lords, holding a wad of papers in both hands.

text: Betty Boothroyd, Baroness Boothroyd OM PC (born 8 October 1929) is a British politician, who served as a Labour Member of Parliament (MP) for West Bromwich and West Bromwich West from 1973 to 1992. From 1992 to 2000, she served as Speaker of the House of Commons. She was the first, and to date only, female Speaker of the House of Commons. She sits, by tradition, as a Crossbench peer in the House of Lords.
